===Etymology===
First attested in the mid 15th century. From {{etyl|enm|en}}, and from {{etyl|xno|en}} {{term|accusatif|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|frm|en}} {{term|acusatif|lang=frm}} or from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|accūsātīvus||of accusing}}, from {{term|accūsātus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{m|la|accūsō}}. The Latin form was mistranslated from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|αἰτιατική|lang=grc}} + {{term|πτῶσις||case of that which was caused|lang=grc}} from {{term|αἰτία||accusation or cause|lang=grc}}. Akin to {{term|accuse|lang=en}}.

